o wrote:
> Hi,
>
> Is there some zsh-specific way to enter utf-8
> characters? Or should I rely on my terminal to
> do that (xterm, mlterm etc.)?
>

You can use insert-composed-char ZLE function; see man zshcontrib.=20
Otherwise there are good chances that it will just work when you enter=20
multibyte characters using OS supplied means.

Keep in mind that zsh will use whatever encoding is set by current=20
locale; it does not convert to UTF-8 internally.

